  <entry>
    <title>Homework #10, due M 11/16</title>
    <author>
      <name>Marco Varisco</name>
      <email>marco@math.binghamton.edu</email>
      <uri>http://www.math.binghamton.edu/marco/</uri>
    </author>
    <id>tag:marco@math.binghamton.edu,2009-11-11:hw10</id>
    <updated>2009-11-11T16:11:00Z</updated>
    <link href="http://www.math.binghamton.edu/marco/topology/#hw10"/>
    <content type="html"><![CDATA[
      A]&nbsp;Show that the lower limit topology on&nbsp;<em>R</em> is
      Hausdorff and first-countable, but not metrizable. (Hint: in
      order to prove that it is not metrizable, show that it
      is&nbsp;&#8230; but not&nbsp;&#8230;, and apply a result
      discussed in class.)<br/>
      B]&nbsp;Show that any set of pairwise disjoint open subsets
      of a separable topological space is countable. <br/>
      C]&nbsp;Show that any discrete subspace
      of a second-countable topological space is countable.
    ]]></content>
  </entry>

